Cuban doctors, who arrived in SA to help fight COVID-19, have completed their 14-day quarantine in Pretoria. The first group has now arrived in the North West Province and is expected to report for duty on Monday. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Cuban doctors, who arrived in SA to help fight COVID-19, have completed their 14-day quarantine in Pretoria. The first group has now arrived in the North West Province and is expected to report for duty on Monday. The Cuban doctors were part of a group that arrived in South Africa last month. WATCH: Cuban doctors not here to take jobs: Mkhize Now, they’re ready to take on the world's most challenging pandemic. The North West health department says the doctors will be stationed in four districts in the province. The Health MEC in the province, Madoda Sambatha, has made it clear that the doctors won’t hijack anyone’s job. Meanwhile, the Cuban doctors, including epidemiologists and healthcare technologists, have vowed to do all they can to help and to work hand in hand with the province's healthcare workers. The provincial government says their last purchase of personal protective gear cost them R88-million. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.